To add another layer of intrigue, top A-League clubs have expressed interest in signing the departing Barcelona captain, Football Federation Australia Chief Executive, David Gallop, has said. Speaking at a media event with the Red Bull Formula One team on Thursday, Iniesta said his next move was complicated, and tha he had much to weigh up before making his decision in the next 10 days. The midfielder also said he wouldn't have a problem with PSG player Neymar, who has been linked with Real Madrid, returning to Barcelona, but said if that did happen he would find it strange. --Reuters--